Former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela says government’s attempts to ensure social justice will remain futile without inclusiveness. Her statement comes on World Day of Social Justice on Tuesday. Madonsela will be take part in a collaborative community event titled ‘Walk in My Shoes’ at the Women’s Jail at Constitution Hill in Johannesburg with the support of the Stellenbosch University Law School. “The clear responsibility in a country like ours is to understand the imbalances of the past, in a country where because of past injustices, there are people who are struck in the cycle of poverty, for example we have more than 50% of our people living in poverty,” Madonsela explains About SABC View all posts by SABC